# HarmonyOS Task Workflow And Documentation Rules

## Task Workflow

- If work is assigned from `.r2mo/task/*.md`, read the Markdown body after frontmatter before changing code.
- If a task explicitly requires a `Changes` section, append that record back into the same task file after implementation.
- Task instructions override generic assumptions when they are specific to the requested work.

## Session Startup

- Read `AGENTS.md` first.
- Read `CLAUDE.md` second.
- Read `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` in lexical order.
- Inspect the target `app-*` directory before editing code.
- Read the target app’s `app.json`, `build-profile.json5`, `entry/src/main/module.json5`, and launch scripts.
- When a build, launch, runtime, or agent workflow problem appears, check `docs/troubleshooting.md` before inventing a new diagnosis path.

## Documentation Sync

- If onboarding, scripts, architecture, runtime UX, or development flow changes, update `AGENTS.md`.
- If onboarding, scripts, architecture, runtime UX, or development flow changes, update `CLAUDE.md`.
- If the change should be machine-loaded early in future sessions, update the relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` topic file.
- Prefer updating only the topical MDC file instead of duplicating the same rule in every file.

## Knowledge Base Documents

- Architecture decisions belong in `docs/adr/` using Status, Context, Decision, and Consequences sections.
- Troubleshooting guidance belongs in `docs/troubleshooting.md` and should include symptoms, root cause, fix steps, and verification commands.
- `app.json` metadata changes should be reflected in `docs/app-json-schema.md`.
- App-level product baselines belong in each app's `REQ.md`.
- Workspace-level notable changes belong in `CHANGELOG.md`.
